The paper discusses model selection and hyperparameter tuning, which are common topics in machine learning. The use of evaluation measures such as AUC, F1, ACC, RMSE, MAD, and cross-entropy suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), or software engineering (cs.SE). The focus on model performance and the introduction of a new rating system for predictive models further supports these sub-categories.
